      "text": " Applying Corollary B, we can establish the truth of Conjecture C unconditionally for primes with small values of  $\\ell_0$ . For instance, if  $1 \\le \\ell_0 \\le 6$  then Conjecture C is true (see, Corollary 2.3, 4.4 and 4.5). Combining the results computed in [MZS14], Theorem A confirms the validity of Conjecture C for a large range of  $\\ell_0$ . For instance, if  $\\ell_0$  is prime power satisfying  $\\ell_0 < 16411$  or if it has two distinct prime divisors such that  $\\ell_0 < 8197$  then Conjecture C is true for prime numbers  $p$  with  $\\ell_0$  satisfying properties just stated (see Theorem 5.1 and Theorem 5.2 for more cases).",
